The paper discusses an efficient neural architecture search approach that incorporates a multi-level architecture encoding scheme and a hierarchical masking scheme. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories, as these are the areas where neural architecture search is commonly used. Additionally, the paper's focus on automatic learning and determining the optimal architecture suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's use of natural language processing (NLP) as an example application suggests that it could also belong to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
